# Line endings.
#
# Git for Windows ships with core.autocrlf=true by default, which rewrites every
# text file to CRLF on checkout. Two things in this repo break when that happens:
#
#   1. The bash scripts (scripts/**/*.sh, skills/**/*.sh) fail to execute under
#      Git Bash or WSL with "bash\r: No such file or directory".
#   2. skills/queue-runner/verify.mjs is a required CI step and parses SKILL.md
#      with LF-literal regexes (e.g. /## Heartbeat Order\n\n([\s\S]*?)\n\n## /).
#      Under CRLF those match nothing, the script throws, and a contributor on
#      Windows cannot reproduce a green CI locally even with correct code.
#      scripts/open-engine/closeout-controller.mjs parses markdown the same way.
#
# So: normalize to LF in the index AND check out LF on every platform. Nothing
# here needs CRLF, and the editors people actually use handle LF fine on Windows.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries: never touch these.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.webp  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.pdf   binary
